Yesterday I posted a question on Facebook asking people “which social media platforms they have gotten off of or just refused to start?”.

Literally, just a question out of curiosity since Threads has recently came on the scene and I’ve already quit it. Lol.

I said “I’ll start….. Telegram, Truth Social and X (Twitter). Just no time for more platforms.”

And Omgosh. Some of the comments. 😢😢

A group of ladies are upset with me because “those are all the conservative platforms“. 

Other people want to know “where do you get the truth for news?”. 

And a handful of people unfollowed me because they thought that the post was political and I think they took it to mean that I am a liberal (which I am absolutely not and I would think would be glaringly obvious). 

I am honestly baffled. 🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️

But here is what I do know. We have a long, long time until the election of 2024. 😫😫

I know that #nationaldaughtersday was yesterday, but I was putting on an event in Dallas all day so today will have to do!!

Backstory: I grew up with 2 brothers. Then I got 4 stepbrothers. My biological father is one of 8 boys and Jason’s father was one of 6 boys. That is ALOT of boys!!!!

After we had 2 boys of our own and then 2 miscarriages…. I wondered if we would ever have a girl??

Truth: I’m obsessed with our sons. They have my whole heart. They can do no wrong. And yet, I wanted daughters too! 

I’ll never forget the day I had a sonogram and the doctor told us we were having a girl. I was so scared to believe it. I had waited so long!!!

We went thru so much warfare to have Ava. It took forever to get pregnant with her. I was “advanced maternal age” 😂. My pregnancy with her was not easy. Early on there was fear of another miscarriage, then gestational diabetes, level 2 sonograms, tests upon tests. 

We literally fought for her to come into this world. 

Ava is God’s literally GIFT to me. I’ve always known that and we even had a pastor tell us that as recently as last week. 
 
I’ll never get over her. She’s a beautiful mess and she’s got the world by the tail. She’s the best parts of her daddy and the best parts of me. 

Many of you have watched Ava grow up on social media. I assure you she is as beautiful inside as she is out.

When Ava was still a newborn we began our adoption journey that I always knew we would be on. 

It took 8 long years of waiting before we got a call about four year old Ariana….. my cousin’s granddaughter. 

We knew she completed our family. She was God’s FAITHFULNESS to me. We had our boys and now we had our girls. 

I can’t look at our family and particularly at our daughters without seeing God’s hand all over it. Some of you know exactly what I’m talking about because you feel the same way about your children. My heart is so full.

He called me “ice queen”. Jokingly of course. But Jason and I were discussing how so often people get such a wrong first impression of me. They think I’m cool. Cold. Stand-off-ish.  It’s been this way all my life. 

Truth: I do not trust easily. I’ll be kind, but closed. Sweet, but guarded. I don’t let people in until I know you are someone I can trust. 

And I only need a few close people who I trust deeply to be happy … my circle is small. 

I’m rarely the one to say hello first or start a friendship. I hide at social events where I don’t know people and am always searching for safe people around me. 

IS THIS YOU TOOOOO? 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️

If you come up to me in public and say hello, there is a 83% chance I will be super awkward and not know what to say or say something weird. 

I don’t like to go out. I love to be home.
I don’t answer my phone. I like to text. 
I love when plans are cancelled. I crave quiet. 

I’m not unsocial…. I’m an INTROVERT.

Now I know you see me on social media so you assume I am outgoing. But most introverts are wayyyyy better on social than we are in real life. 

And I know you just saw me host a live event for 20 women and wonder how I can do that as an introvert? I do those things not because I’m comfortable but because it helps my clients. I just make myself to hard things.

I share this because:

a) I want to warn you in case we happen to bump into each other out in the wild. I’ll be weird and quiet. Jason will be amazing and talk your leg off. Thank goodness for him! 😂

And …

b) I want you other introverts to know you can totally be successful at coaching and selling online too. Do not think that the way God wired you is wrong. I promise being an introvert can be your secret sauce (go listen to last week’s podcast). 

It took me a good 40 years before I really understood how I was wired and how I need to interact with others in order to feel safe. 

If that is you tonight, I hope this post helps you feel like you’re not alone. I hope that even if you have been misunderstood that you feel at peace.

One of the things that I dislike the most about December is the increase of the “push harder” / “finish strong” / “don’t let up now” types of posts. 

Being a business owner is full of enough pressure. And I hate the additional pressure upon pressure that well-meaning coaches put out every holiday season. 🙈🙈

Should you “push hard” from now to the end of the year? I say only if you have the capacity. 

Should your goal be to “finish strong”? Well absolutely. But often for me “finishing strong” means finishing rested, finishing peaceful, finishing present. 🙏🙏

Sometimes “don’t let up now” is just terrible advice. You have not worked your butt off all year only to have to accelerate even harder over the holiday season. No. Nope. No way. 🤢🤢

It is absolutely insane how many people can hustle their faces off, but cannot take any time off. 

I always wonder… What are they running from? 
Who are they hiding from? 
What on earth are they working this hard for if they can’t walk away for a few days or weeks? 

Don’t fall for the lie my friends.  You can either push or pause during this season. It’s your choice! 

I just encourage you to do what makes sense for you and your family and your heart and your peace. 

And with absolutely no guilt. 

THAT is finishing the year strong. 😘

The 30 or 40 year old me would never have done this. 🙈🙈

I never traveled alone until the last few years. And certainly never traveled alone just for pleasure. 

For a long time our kids were just way too little, Jason worked all.the.time and I told myself we couldn’t afford it and it would be a childcare mess (all true). But the bigger truth is I felt guilty about leaving them. 

And I never wanted to travel without my husband because I like to travel WITH him and what would it say about our marriage if I went alone? 

What would people think? Would they assume that things were not good at home if I was leaving him and the children behind? 

But then Jason has an accident 2 years ago that prevented him from traveling a bunch. And we bought 2 Airbnb properties during that time that I had to renovate and decorate…. so suddenly I was traveling often… alone. 

And you know what. I loved it. I LOVE to travel. I crave seeing new things. Plus as an introvert I need alot of alone time and recovery time….. especially the older I get. 

Jason is the total opposite as an extrovert. He loves people and chaos which I need a break from. PLUS WE WORK TOGETHER AT HOME ALL DAY EVERY DAY TOGETHER. 😂😂

I mean, I’m obsessed with my husband, but absence can really make the heart grow fonder. 😂😂

Jason can tell when the day to day in the business and just the pressures of life in general are becoming too heavy for me. And he knows there is nothing like the beach to clear my mind and quiet my soul.

And so now I travel alone… without fear or guilt. 

He says I come back a much nicer person and he’s right! lol

Sharing with you ladies because some of you are being buried alive under the pressures of business and home right now. And I get it. 

➡️➡️ But just because you carry it well doesn’t mean it isn’t heavy. ⬅️⬅️

Take care of yourself friend. Lighten your load. Retreat if you need to. The house and the fam and the biz can all do without you for a few days if that’s what you need. I wish I had done this years ago. 

Anyone else travel solo?????

2023 was not an easy year for me. As I sit and ponder all that we’ve gone through as a family and me personally this year, it feels heavy. Discouraging.

Personal stuff. Family stuff. Extended family stuff. Financial stuff. Work stuff. Health stuff. 

Stuff that never makes it to social media. Lol. 

And you get it. None of us get out of this life without going through seasons that are just…. tough. (Matt 5:45)

I have probably spent way too much time at the end of this year licking my wounds. Worrying. Wallowing if you will. 🙈🙈

I think when you’re in a tough season it’s so easy to just mentally keep clicking through all that is going wrong or has gone wrong. 

But I have to re-center myself at the end of every year because I know that “the way we end one season is also the way we will go into the next season.”

And I don’t want to flip the calendar page tomorrow and still feel like I feel TODAY. 

So I’m sharing with you a discipline I’ve done every year since our kids were little! My list of “top 10 blessings from the past year”. 

The Bible tells us to “record and remember” several times. It’s impossible not to list out so many amazing things that happened in the last year and then also continue to pout over the things that did not.

As I began to go back in my camera roll on my phone this morning and look at the last year….my list of top 10 blessings quickly turned into my top 19. 

19 things that I could think of off the top of my head where God showed up and blew my socks off this year. 

THAT is what I want to ponder on for the rest of today. Not how badly I want this year to end…… but instead how grateful I am for everything that it held. 

Because I think for many of us…. 2023 held pain and beauty both.
Discouragement and blessing both.
Loss and gain both.

And I want to spend the day focusing on the good. 

Especially because I know that “A grateful heart is a breeding ground for miracles.”

If we concentrate and dwell on our current situation.... things can get and look a little wonky.
